SURULERE Local Government Area of Lagos State yesterday presented a N3.1 billion budget to the legislative arm. Council Chairman Sulaiman Yusuf said the proposed budget would ensure the people enjoyed more dividends of democracy. He said his administration had delivered infrastructural development, free health services and empowerment, among others.   ‘Why Nigeria needs Tinubu now’     Reps urge IG to probe alleged attacks, killings by security…     Festschrift: Tinubu, Afe Babalola, others laud Akinfeleye’s…   Yusuf said: “We hope the economy would be better in the current year despite the third wave of the global pandemic. Our budget is predicted on the economic benchmark of Federal Government budget since a large chunk of our revenue (about 80 per cent) comes from federal account, most of which is determined by crude oil price, oil benchmark, GDP Growth Rate, inflation rate, exchange rate etc. “However, given the Federal Government’s economic benchmarks and zeal to maximise independent revenue, we are on course for sustainable development as we remain committed to the actualisation of our vision for a brighter, promising and prosperous future for all residents through the construction of new legislative building, rehabilitation of the council secretariat, among others…” - Advertisement - The chairman reiterated his commitment to ensuring sustainable development in line with the T.H.E.M.E.S agenda of Governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu.